===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|㚔|丮|t1=criminal / handcuffs|t2=hand|ls=ic}}: to [[arrest]]. In the present form, {{zh-l|㚔}} and {{zh-l|丮}} have been replaced by {{zh-l|幸}} and {{zh-l|丸}}, respectively.

===Etymology===
Possibly related to {{cog|bo|ཆབ|t=power; dominion}} or {{cog|km|ចាប់|t=to grasp; to seize}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler 2007}}). {{ncog|ko|집다|집-|t=to pick up; to grab}} is probably coincidental.
; “to go bankrupt and close down”
: {{zh-etym-short|執笠}}.

